NextCLOUD STORAGE PROJECT (AWS EC2) — FULL IMPLEMENTATION DOCUMENTATION

🌍 Project Overview
/This project sets up a self-hosted cloud storage system on an AWS EC2 Ubuntu server using:

Apache Web Server
MariaDB Database
PHP (8.5 default on modern Ubuntu)
Nextcloud (cloud storage platform)

❗ WHY NEXTCLOUD INSTEAD OF OWNCLOUD
🚫 OwnCloud Problem
OwnCloud failed because of PHP incompatibility:

This server runs on: PHP 8.5 while
OwnCloud supports: PHP ≤ 8.0 / 8.1
Result: ❌ Installation blocked

✅ Why Nextcloud is the correct choice
Nextcloud was chosen because:

✔ PHP compatibility
Works with PHP 8.3 / 8.4 / 8.5 (modern systems)
✔ Actively maintained
Frequent updates and security patches
✔ Better ecosystem
More apps (calendar, contacts, talk, collaboration tools)
✔ Industry standard
Used by enterprises and governments
✔ Same purpose
File storage, sharing, sync, user management

👉 Conclusion: Nextcloud is the modern replacement for OwnCloud

🏗️ FULL IMPLEMENTATION STEPS
y
🟢 PHASE 1 — AWS EC2 SETUP
1. Launch EC2 Instance
OS: Ubuntu Server (latest)
Instance type: t2.micro or higher
Storage: default (20GB recommended)

2. Security Group Rules
Allow:

SSH (22) → Your IP only
HTTP (80) → 0.0.0.0/0
HTTPS (443) → optional later

🟢 PHASE 2 — CONNECT TO SERVER
From Windows PowerShell:

ssh -i "OwnCloud-Key.pem" ubuntu@13.61.8.230

🟢 PHASE 3 — SYSTEM UPDATE
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Expected Outcome

✔ Updates system packages
✔ Applies security patches
⚠️ System reboot warning appears (ignored temporarily)

🟢 PHASE 4 — INSTALL APACHE (WEB SERVER)
sudo apt install apache2 -y
Verify:
apache2 -v

Expected Outcome

✔ Apache installed successfully

🟢 PHASE 5 — INSTALL PHP (DEFAULT VERSION)
sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php php-mysql php-cli php-curl php-gd php-xml php-mbstring php-zip unzip -y

Expected Outcome

✔ PHP 8.5 installed automatically


🟢 PHASE 6 — INSTALL MARIADB DATABASE
sudo apt install mariadb-server mariadb-client -y
Secure MariaDB
sudo mariadb-secure-installation

Steps:

Set root password ✔
Remove anonymous users ✔
Remove test DB ✔
Disable remote root login ✔
Reload privileges ✔

🟢 PHASE 7 — CREATE DATABASE FOR NEXTCLOUD

Enter MariaDB:

sudo mariadb

Run:

CREATE DATABASE owncloud;
CREATE USER 'ownclouduser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'Physical123/';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON owncloud.* TO 'ownclouduser'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;

✔ Database created
✔ User created
✔ Permissions granted

🟢 PHASE 8 — DOWNLOAD NEXTCLOUD
cd /tmp
wget https://download.nextcloud.com/server/releases/latest.zip

mkdir ~/nextcloud-install
cd ~/nextcloud-install
mv /tmp/latest.zip .
unzip latest.zip

✔ Extraction successful

🟢 PHASE 10 — DEPLOY NEXTCLOUD
sudo mv nextcloud /var/www/html/
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html/nextcloud
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/nextcloud

🟢 PHASE 11 — ENABLE APACHE MODULES
sudo a2enmod rewrite headers env dir mime
sudo systemctl restart apache2

Expected Outcome

✔ Apache configured for Nextcloud

🟢 PHASE 12 — VERIFY SERVER STATUS
sudo systemctl status apache2

Expected Outcome

✔ Apache running correctly

🟢 PHASE 13 — FINAL ACCESS

Open in browser:

http://13.61.8.230/nextcloud

